at he wanted for so long he had character customisation, free form skill tree progression with the ability to change to a different variety of weapons without being stuck with one class, men who played as women and jumped around alot and most importantly he had no idea what he was doing. Despite all this he was happy... and well how do I know he was happy you may be asking?I am that guy. (Of course you've already likely figuired that out so no suprise there)Serious ReviewFor a game in early access I find it pretty fun it has main functionality and the devs are looking to add much more content before release so that's looking dandy.The combat is like most MMO setups but does offer a Third-Person Shooter mode it isn't grand but it makes a nice change. The ability to be able to rank up and use all weapon types greatly pleases me too many times I have felt restricted by other games due to their enforcement of a specific class, although it was fun to start with the novelty and the wanting to use other weapons grew.With Character customisation you are able to modify your face and build etc, there are a limited amount of hair styles at present but enough to keep most satisfied such as myself. A nice feature I have found was upon visiting a store I was able to purchase a cheap cosmetic item to change my facial structure this greatly pleases me as I always screw up something in my characters in all games.Being a Social / Sandbox MMO you are able to do a variety of things I have seen dancers, crafters, people on floaty bike things reminicent of the Scout Trooper bikes from Star Wars. You can also cook, build robots etc.There are some issues with Repop such as weird little feet indicators that clip through your clothing however these are barely noticible unless you are wearing specific clothing, I also imagine this will be dealt with at some point in the near future. Other issues would be new comers at least in my experiance might not be sure what to do, it took me a while to figuire out the NPCs could help me locate mission based NPCs when they weren't on my map for a quest. All in all though for an alpha it is pretty good and it looks promising. I have seen data that suggests it will be coming out as Free 2 Play so you may wish to just wait till its fully released and not drop a penny but if you are like myself and don't mind some bugs, helping out devs and getting early access then it might be up your street."
