76561197960403453,Recommended,322300,17496715,"Posted: 11 August, 2015",all,soupy21,"It's a great game. Fun to play, and the community is great. When you ask questions in General Chat, you typically get great answers and lots of help. Sometimes questions develop into larger discussions between more experienced players, and you learn even more.Crafting is deep, and develops over time. Vehicles, animal pets, robot pets, genetically engineered pets, guild housing, player housing, PvP large and small, this game has it all.This truly is a sandbox play-it-your way kind of game. No need to grind to Level 100 before you get to the ""fun stuff"". Start developing your combat skills right away, and within a short amount of time you will be strong and rich enough to outfit your character enough to tackle large group content. There are no traditional raids, but there are areas of the game where you'll find a ""Miniboss"" for 3-4 players, ""Boss"" for 5-8 players, ""Raid Boss"" for 10-16 players, ""Ultra Raid Boss"" for 24+ players. All in the open world. Fight creatures 10x your size!Do note that this game is currently in late Alpha phase, and Early Access. Yes the game has bugs, and frustrating patches. But you also have the benefit of seeing this great game grow and develop over time.Ever play a brand new game and there's some elite group of players that say things like ""I've been playing this for years"" or ""Things used to be different! Remember X Y Z"". Those players are from the Alpha and Beta phases of the game. Now is your chance to join those elite players before this game gets very popular."
