,Recommended,322300,14604359,"Posted: 22 February, 2015",all,bluefootedpig,"While I haven't played much in this game, I am only really waiting until the release to dive deep into this game. It has so much, and what is best is that you don't feel limited. You aren't a ""class"". I can spend time fishing with buddies, each of us working on our skill, then I can go off hunting.The game has no skill cap, but rather has diminishing returns on the odds of getting a skill up. So the long term players will be better, but that gap means less as you get higher up.The crafting is insane, basically you can't make things from start to finish, well you can, but it won't turn out well. Each item made is often used in another process to make something else. Each step of the process takes into account the crafters skill with that specific receipe. This means you can be awesome at making batteries, but horrible at refining ore.This means you can work a niche. I have met people who are basically only doing a few items, and they made good money.The bard buffs (dancing) seem nice.I recommend this game to people who don't like class systesm, want a very niche type crafting system, and more or less just someone who doesn't want to feel like they wasted time by helping a friend."
