,Recommended,322300,14413080,"Posted: 9 February, 2015",all,Durai,"If you like Star Wars :Galaxies you would love this, its basicly the same thing just...well just more amazing! Great game so far, ran into very few bugs as an alpha game.Now im updating this since i have the time,There are lots of neat features that alot of players from SW:G would see.Skills: This is the primary element of the game, Skills progress as you play. The more you shoot Automatic weaponry, The more it goes up. The more you harvest Plants the more your Flora skill goes up, The more you craft weaponry, ect. This makes the game more time consuming yes, but at the same time you do not have to put a full 12 hours of gameplay to progress, For instance if you only have 2 hours a day to game you can still get to do things others do, Granted it will take you longer than someone who spends 12-18 hours a-day but still you can do it too with no restrictions other than your time.Gameplay: This element of the game can be played majority in two ways, RPG mode; Simple understanding, Movement keys work and you use your mouse and keyboard to play like you would in World of Warcraft.[ Not comparing just saying that you use number keys to use skills and what not]So basicly your standard MMO controls almost with key differnces that are easily seen when you play.Action Mode: This mode is my personal fav when it comes to combat. This mode turns the game into a Fake shooter, You aim with the mouse you get a crosshair and you attack with your left and right mouse buttons. There are ALOT of bonuses to this, If using guns you can AIM and hit Certain areas dealing more or less damage. making combat more fast pace you can still use # keys for skills, The only thing that changes ins the control scheme.So i use RPG mode for everything else but combat mostly. If i feel lazy i will use RPG to attack. In RPG mode damage is mostly chest as spread is wider in RPG mode with guns. (This as if firing a gun from the hip its more inaccurate yeah?)Sandbox Features: These features plays a major role later on, I have yet to buy one i am working on my offical character now but with these features you can do several things, so far what i can tell there are going to be Three memberships which are all going to be a ONETIME PAYMENT, Silver, Gold, Plat. Gold and Plat can both make towns/cities while plat will get access to Nation. Not sure as this is Early Access so i do not know the Release prices. Nations are part of the Sandbox features as this makes you a Rouge faction, This is a playermade faction. (Sorta like guilds) Now i know what everyone is thinking. ""OH GREAT I HAVE TO PAY REAL CASH TO HAVE A GUILD"" You may have to MAKE ONE, but joining a nation that exist is going to be the better option early on, as a Nation your going to have alot more problems. Such as the old faction likly to start hating you more. (You deserted what'cha expect Cake and cookies? This aint no girl scout army) You will be able to make houses with out needing to pay at all. housing will let you do several things, Craft, Party, Live. housing lets you place Crafting devices, Decorate, Invite your friends over and entertain them and ect. so this is one of the fun features. No info on towns/cities yet.No combat needed: This is added to the game where you do not ever need to swing a sword, Fist,shoot a gun ever. You can do all the crafting and everything not involing combat if thats what you want with out ever equiping weapons.Now onto the Cons i see of this game.Grindy!: This game is grindy beyond grindy. Skills require you to use that skill stuff to advance it.Lengthy: This game needs people who are Dedicated to playing when they can, Otherwise you wasted your time even looking at the game, But if you think you would like it give it a try but make sure your willing to try to put time and effort into the game.Slow: This game is not going to let you max your skills in a week, a month, or likely in a year, If you were to focus on one skill it would likely take you six months to max it out and from what ive heard, the skills max out at 60,000 points, and you gain your skill one point at a time.Alpha: This game being in alpha is a Con unto its self, its a great game so, if your not willing to support and report bugs and such, Dont even bother with the game IT IS NOT COMPLETE!Huge amount of skills: Over 75 different skills to use, and you can use em all. But to master EVERY skill would take even the most constant gamer  years to do so. Its like Eve online They do not go easy on you.The pros of the game are a smaller list but more impactful.Nice Community: The community is nice and helpful, there is always someone there to help you.Great gameplay: the gameplay is amazing and the Random gen quests dont stop, Always something to do.Amazing stability: There are so few game breaking bugs as far as i can tell, Ive ran into the minor/annoying bugs and a few Quest stoppers. But for this game being in alpha its great. Never crashed once."
