,Recommended,322300,15192507,"Posted: 3 April, 2015",all,KG_Middian,"I don't really write reviews much any more unless a game is extremely bad or extremely good since Repop falls under one of these categories here I goRating 15/10Yes that's right you see it 15/10 is the rating I give Repop and I'll you'll find out whyRepop is a Sci-fi sandbox mmo that in my eye's is more of an amazing futuristic VR world feel perfectly combined with all the RPG elements we love and on top of that they expand and made every system their own.Repop gets a 10 out of 10 just for being amazing and allowing you complete freedom and systems that are not only unique but perfectly set up.  The extra 5 points is for the fact that with all it's greatness it's still in early access beta which is impressive.  Most alpha's I enter always end up with the game being unplayable whereas Repop is not.  Keep in mind there is bugs, and stuff going haywire from time to time but the bug reporting system in game and on the forums are constantly watched, there's even GM's in game pretty much 24hours a day for in game help and most of the time the GM's have your problem fixed without you even needing to leave the game.I definately suggest you drop all the games your playing and get this game but before you do I have a few tips for starting out.REPOP is not your traditional ""handholding"" rpg, you are not guided to your next step.  it's more of a here's what you need to survive , and ya get kicked out the door.   Some people find this frustrating others love it the best way to look at it I think is to think of it this way, say you get your memory wiped and get dropped off in a different country where nobody knows you what do you do? Well ya don't just sit there and whine about it you get off your but and do what you can to survive, make money, and work your way up the ladder, well that's Repop.When you first get into the game after you created your character and everything you will be put into the tutorial area.  This area is where you will learn the basics of playing this game.  In most MMO's gamers generally just click through the chatting and use the mission tracker and map to do the quests this technique might work well in other games but DO NOT click through,  read everything you can , absorb all the information given to you in the tutorial zone because if you don't you'll spend hours out in the real world going ""How the hell"" and spend more time figuring it out that it would've taken you to listen to the trainer.Along with the fact that this game is decades ahead of any other game I've played (which is a lot) in terms of systems, features and game mechanics it's definately a must buy and the community of players repop has drawn in are an amazing bunch, they are helpful, active, dedicated , and understand the importance of community and ultimately it's that aspect that makes or breaks a game.Repopulation is amazing definately worth every penny the Devs, Community , support and GM's are the best their is and really dedicated to bringing the best experience to all of us"
