,Recommended,322300,18756121,"Posted: 29 October, 2015",all,Ranch Dubois,"This is a fantastic scifi sandbox mmorpg that really gave me a feeling I haven't felt since the pre-combat upgrade days of Star Wars Galaxies.  Literally one of the only things I see holding this game back is the lack of a community. There are maybe 50 people on the US server that are online at a time, so it's hard for new players to get the proper support from others that they need. Not only that, but a lot of the game depends on player to player interactions, especially when it comes to crafting and the auction house, so it can be difficult for players who may want to play a non-combat role in the game to get the materials that they need. That's why I want to encourage everyone who enjoys this genre of mmo to support the development and buy into the alpha now.  Anyway, here's why the game is awesome:-Huge maps to explore, barely any instances at all! Nearly Seamless!!!-amazingly indepth crafting system.-leveling the right way! instead of your character having a base level, every single type of gear, weapon, armor, skill, you name it... has its own level that has to be leveled the good old fashioned way, by practicing it. Using a particular skill or item will level that specific thing, so if you shoot a lot of pistols you gain experience in pistol tactics, you use light armor you get light armor tactics, etc.- (this one is a pro and a con) Community dependant. It thrives when there is a huge player base, which it does not have at the moment. There are building plots, which allow for entire player built cities to be placed. There is so many different crafting skills to choose from and sooooo many different components needed to craft these different things that it makes it difficult when there aren't many crafting components for sale on the auction house. Please support the game, the developers, and the community to make this game even better!I mentioned this earlier but it really does bring me back to the Galaxies pre-CU days. It's not an exact clone of SWG, but it does follow in the footsteps as an amazing sandbox mmo."
