76561197980793947,Recommended,322300,16772980,"Posted: 28 June, 2015",all,Solego,"It takes a lot for me to actually like an MMO enough to actually want to go out there and say, ""Hey, world!  Yea, you!  Get this game.""  I will start out by saying that if you've ever played and liked Star Wars Galaxies, this game will fill the gaping wound that Sony Online left in your life.  'nuff said, there.  If you liked SWG then get this game.For everyone that has not played SWG, a bit of a gameplay walkthrough.  The game starts out very well for an alpha MMO, with a fully featured newbie area and tutorials enough to give you a really good foundation of all the skills a new player may want to play with.  You get basic training in several weapon types for free and the ability to spend training credits on up to three others, with the ability to choose from any weapon type the game has to offer. You also get basic crafting tutorials that give you enough of an idea how the surprisingly complex crafting system works to get you on your feet, and gives you a preview of how the really complex things will work once you get that far.  You are also introduced to Entertaining, for providing temporary buffs to allies; Stealth and Rouge-like options, like trap detection and disarming; Animal Taming and Robotic pets; and Medical skills.  And as you play through the tutorial area you get a feel for just how much more there is to play with as you progress with the game.  With dozens of different skills across 6 different catagories.  Even with the comprehensive tutorials, the game is overwhelming at first.  This game has a LOT of mechanics, although they are not so bad that they get in your way.I definitely recommend it for anyone that's tired of the cookie cutter WoW clones that have been coming out for the last few years.  They definitely stray from the textbook MMO here and it is so refreshing."
76561197987152970,Not Recommended,322300,13689302,"Posted: 29 December, 2014",all,Conga-Line Bob,"EDIT-1/26/16 - The developer has shut down the servers and they're not exactly being forthcoming with the reasons why. According to their website they have run into an issue with their hosting company with regards to new account creation. They have completely suspended development and shut down the servers with no ETA as to when business would resume. They promise that they're going to continue to develop the game and bob loblaw. My review which i wrote a long time ago stated that I felt that the development team was inept. From the graphics, to the implementation, the audio, and everything else it was just a really bad game. While they do say that they aren't abandoning the game, I do believe this is another sign of their ineptitude. Don't buy this game if it goes on sale again. It's really bad.I have popped in now and again over the past year or so and I obviously stay current with the news of the game. I can once again state with confidence that this game is NOT going anywhere. Another poorly fleshed out MMO that will see it's demise likely before it even begins. Stay away.This game is ugly, clunky, confusing, repetitive, bug riddled, and boring. I'm generally willing to overlook issues that others are not. But man, this game gives me a headache. Not because it's hard, because it isn't - but the graphics, UI, map, and minimap are just all so poorly implemented that it literally makes my head throb in pain.The Audio is awful. I work in the audio industry and i'd be embarrassed if this were my sound design work. The quality of the sound effects are bad. The music flutters in the game and needs to be muted.The graphics in this game are mixed. The 3D player art is really nice. Beyond that it's between bad and laughable. People argue that it's early access or alpha so graphics shouldn't be considered. I think those people are wrong as i've been a part of a ton of alpha's and early access games where the grahpics showed promise. What i'm looking at is certainly not representative of the final product but it is representative of the art teams talent. In this case i'd say the art team is not talented.The UI consists of a ton of menu diving. Little boxes with tabs that extend out of site. I'm forced to open little windows and click a little arrow key to get to the tab I need which consumes quite a bit oftime. These information menu's are things that you need to access constantly. It becomes annoying and adds to the tediousness of this game. Keep in mind that i'm a 10 year Eve vet. People jokingly refer to Eve as ""world of spreadsheets""... so I can deal with data. I imagine that these things will be refined over time.The minimap is a tiny little circle that shows little detail in the terrain. NPC's, monsters, players, quest items are little tiny dots. They are everywhere and it needs a lot of improving. In all honesty it should be scrapped. Around the minimap you have little yellow arrows that tell you which directions to go for quests you have. Only problem is that they blend in with the terrain or with some of the icons aroundthe minimap so you can't even see them. Literally they disappear. I expect this is something that will be changed shortly cause right now it's just a clusterf**k of dots.The map itself is a little more useful. By pressing M you get a little map window, that's notexpandable, that shows you your immediate surroundings. I had complained that the map was terrible because itdidn't scroll. Someone from the development team commented on my review that by pressing ""Shift-M"" you get a scrolling map. He was correct but the map is still bad. It's a tinly little box, that doesn't appear to expand, that's about 1/8th the size of your screen. Even if it did expand it shows very little detail, is ugly, and causes my framerate to drop very low.The combat is clunky and the way it's implemented I basically can't use any of my skills. You have to right click your target to shoot and left click items on your bar to activate them. Maybe i'm missing something but that's not my fault. This games just so clunky and confusing, including the tutorial, that it's not obvious in any way. I have found that by assigning some of my abilites to extra mouse buttons is really the only way to go. For people who don't have a fancy mouse with extra buttons then i'd say that you'll be at a distinct disadvantage compared to those that do. Also the combat is not fun or challenging. Combat consists of right clicking on your target.The gameplay is very repetitive. Questing is like WoW. Though you receive quests through an email system the meat of the quests are the same. Go to location X, gather resource Y, deliver to NPC Z. Or Kill 8 of these and return to NPC X. Or pick up package at NPC X and deliver to NPC Z. That's fine because that's not really what this game is about. However, it adds to the repetitive feeling of this game.Resource gathering thus far has consisted of running out of the town, finding nodes which are clustered by the dozens in specific areas, and harvesting one after another after another after another. There is no real danger, there is no real challenge, and it's very repetitive. From what i've experienced thus far it's completely a solo activity.Crafting has been much of the same experience. You can only craft at a ""crafting station"". These are situated inside cities and you generally find a number of people all huddled around it. You find the item you want to craft in your recipe book, place items in window, and you get your crafted item. There is a fairly deep crafting system that is somewhat rewarding. I think this is where a lot of the potential in this game lies. I've been following the advice of the tutorial and sticking with one profession. Generally that's the right thing to do in all MMO's but I find the process of gathering resources in the game extremely boring. I find that crafting in this game is extremely boring. This does not appeal to me though in other games I enjoy carebear acitivities.Hopefully more people read the negative reviews and think twice. I bought this game because of the positive reviews and the pretty pictures. BIG MISTAKE. I understand that hardcore SWG fans have been waiting for this game for a while. I'm glad that they have a new home. I am not one of the SWG refugees.Yes, it's alpha and yes the developers have intentions of improving this game. Well they better because as it sits now it's a bad game. So many good games out there and in my library. This game isn't one of them.If you're on the fence about this game my advice would be to just wait and see. Watch the lets play videos as they surface and follow the development and updates as they occur.I for one am very excited about the ""potential"" of this game. I don't feel like I was ripped off or that I wasted my money. This is an ambitious project. Considering that this game was made thus far by a small development team and very limted funds (like less than 100k i'm being told) it is quite impressive. That being said, when you fork over your 35 bucks you're doing it in good faith that the developer is going to do something positive with it. As it sits right now it's not fun and many others will share my feelings.Sorry if the sensitive gamers were offended by my review. I'm just offering my experience and opinion. My opinion is not wrong and neither is yours! We're talking about games here..."
