,Recommended,322300,15149991,"Posted: 31 March, 2015",all,Shamshire,"Oh boy, where to start.I freakin' love this game, let me get that out there first but I recognize it isn't for everyone.  If you like old school MMOs and have gotten tired or burned out on more recent MMOs where your existance in the game is largely running errands for NPCs, this one could interest you.Fair warning, there be a learning curve ahead.I've put 60 hours into the game at the time of writing and have so barely scratched the surface, it's laughable.  As I slowly learn more and more about the game, I start to like it more and more.  The crafting system is very complex and the different discilplines are tied together so one person cannot easily do everything, which forces cooperation within a group or buying materials from other players on the auction house.  It's not as simple as collect the resources, click a button, and poof I have my brown leggings of might!  The quality of the resource matters, how familiar your character is with the recipe matters, your character's skill in that profession matters.There are no limits on what your character can do.  Mastering a ""profession"" requires an enormous amount of time so it really just comes down to what do you want to spend your time doing.  Want to learn how to tame and control animals?  Do it.  Want to craft weapons or armors?  Do it.  The more you do it, the better you get.  Tons of areas to level your character, you'll never reach the end.I could go on but I'll put it bluntly: This is a complex game that requires some time but if you invest. it becomes extremely rewarding.  It may be comforting to know the community is very friendly and helpful and GMs are active in General and Newbie chat to help you figure out the game."
,Recommended,322300,14874932,"Posted: 13 March, 2015",all,FeelinHawt,"Before you buy this game read the posative AND negative reviews.  I would not say this game is for everyone, but if it is for you, you'll love it.The way they go about skills is unique to modern MMO's. You can be a melee'r with a sheild who stealths gets some distance pull a gun out and blast on your enemys from afar if you so wish. Or maybe you want to be a healer who buffs has a sheild with 3 pets defending you and heck, why not throw in the stealth skill while you're at it. (I like stealth) Maybe you just want to dance and talk in chat, the choice is yours. Mix and match as you please. The map is big and they keep adding more areas and points of interest. There are 3 ways to sell or buy items involving other players. 1.) Player venders 2.) Work orders 3.) Auction House. These 3 ways leave an opening to become a master of the economy if you want to. Crafting is deep to say the least but I'm not much of a crafter so I won't get into that but every item you can use is made by other players, if it's high quality. The community is helpful most of the time, people want the community to learn the game and keep playing it.  The armors are shells meaning you can wear what you want and put fitting in them to increase your stats, same with the guns. If you find a look you like keep it as long as you like just change the fittings in and out. There's player citys and in later updates seige warfare (seigeing has been disabled for now) and remeber player citys have peices made by other players as well as the seige weapons. Mastering skills can take some time so don't expect to jump in and be the master of stealth, healing, entertaining, construction, harvesting, buffing, animal handling, robotics, combat and more. It's best to pick a few that complement each other and level them. Heck even vehicle handling is a skill.  There are 73 skills (give or take) listed on theirwebsiteand one that isn't (that I know of) spirital arts. All 73 skills are broken up into 6 categories. Like I said mix and match.I play this game on a 4 year old laptop with an onboard graphics chipset. My CPU runs at 1.3ghz duel core. So when this game goes F2P expect alot of people to at the very least try it.  Although Be Warned! This game plans to do a server wipe once it is released. If you don't like the sound of that, just wait for it's release."
,Recommended,322300,13930057,"Posted: 10 January, 2015",all,Morphius,i believe this game is great and has huge potential to finally replace my starwars galaxies that i played for years. I would recommend this game to those that have played starwars galaxies and love that social side of it with mayor and player towns etc.
76561198084739818,Recommended,322300,15771907,"Posted: 10 May, 2015",all,Mazael,"This game has steadily (about once every 2 months there is a large patch.)  been making great progress ever sense initial alpha 1.   Alot of people call it ""vapor ware"" but it is a smaller stuido making a very complex and interesting game.   Bottom line this is an alpha but its in great condition for an alpha.  It does have bugs yes but the core features are implemented and there is plenty to keep anyone busy.Is this game for you? Maybe maybe not.  This is the true spiritual successor to SWG.  The crafting system is the most complex and challenging (in a good way) crafting system ive ever seen in an MMO.  It is also the most rewarding crafting system due to this.  When you actually accomplish producing something you feel as if you have accomplished a great task.This is also a sandbox no hand holding here folks.  It does have a basic tutorial to get you introduced to the game but after that you better be able to tell your on tale and make goals on your own as to what you want to do.Overall 8/10 right now due to alpha i will hold my 10/10 for release.  Would have paid more to play it and been perfectly happy."
