,Recommended,322300,14766590,"Posted: 6 March, 2015",all,Vauhn,"Initial Review:I will keep this brief, but add to it as I play. I have completed the initial tutorial for the game and am starting to progress through my chosen craft. Generally I prefer crafting, but do enjoy combat from time to time, so I went with Genetic Engineer. I supply my own Tissue and DNA samples which you get from harvesting animals, which need to be dead. I have dabbled into some of the other crafts and have quickly realized how intense the crafting in this game really is. It is very difficult to become your own supplier.For instance, I can buy sterilizing agents(agent A), but I decide to craft them, so I determine which profession makes them. Turns out several, so I pick Chemistry, to make agent A, I need another item made with chemistry(agent B), as well as a raw resource, and an Acid(Agent C). So I go to make Agent B and find it requires another Raw resources and another agent from another skill(Agent D). For Agent C I need another craft skill, foraging, so I pick that up to find that I need a raw resource and more of Agent B. To make agent D I need A Raw resource, and who knows what else, so I just buy it. So to make a simple item, needed to make anything else in Genetic Engineering, I need 4 different raw materials, and 5 different crafting sessions, and that is with buying one refined item, which I need twice. I may still be missing a step, but to get those 4 different Raw materials, I need Foraging, Survival, Mining. I would also need a combat skill to be able to kill the creatures for some of those items. I guess if I wanted to keep it brief, I should not have mentioned the crafting system.That said, it is a very well done system and it is exciting to see your work progress. I am ten hours in and have forgotten that there was no class selection, and the world feels very free and open, a much better feel for an mmo in my opinion. However, its not all sunshine and rainbows either. There are glitches, random crashes, graphical anomolies and everything else you would expect to find in a game. I have not knowingly joined a group(more on that later) or participated in PVP so I cannot speak on game balance. That said, it is definately worth the money, just remember you are basically buying a product that is still in Alpha. You are helping a startup to fund a brilliant idea and they almost always have a GM on to answer questions or help with bugs, which shows their commitment to making this game a success.I am still listing it as a con because it is hard to find but here is some good information for new players.http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=362788661- Pros -Amazing crafting systemEnjoyable combatGood TutorialGreat Trade SystemComplex Skill TreeGM Support- Cons -Learning Curve (A manual would be nice, especially for the UI)Auto Group (realized I was in a group for the first time yesterday)Glitches (expected but a con none the less)"
