,Recommended,322300,17495136,"Posted: 11 August, 2015",all,Dreye,"The Repopulation is an open world, sci-fi sandbox game currently in early access that has continual updates and a helpful community. As of now the game is coming along nicely, the crafting is complicated and fullfilling and while in need of some UI streaming it hits the nail on the head for those who enjoy carving their mark on a player driven econony. Combat is fluid (as long as there is no lag) and feels smooth with practice, there will still be moments when you are killed outright by a mob and dont quite understand why your new weapon is not working as you expected untill you realise you didnt upgrade it or that mob type has resistances to your damage type.While this game is easy to pickup, it is also quite complicated and has a medium/high learning curve. It can be daunting starting out with no real clear goal until you find your stride and decide what you want to be and achieve. As of now the population is low due to alpha character wipes that will occur in the not too distant future so it is a great time to jump in and learn how things work.There are bugs and moments of lag that will be ironed out in the coming months no doubt by the dedicated developers, so just realise this when you jump in and something strange happens out of the ordinary. Players looking for an MMO that combines dedication to a server run economy who are looking for a deeper experience may enjoy this game very much but be aware, lots of reading on how things work is definately recommended before hand, check out some wikis and player made videos to brush up on the game."
