76561198021314205,Recommended,322300,14940613,"Posted: 17 March, 2015",all,Eleraan,"At the time of writing this I have put in 266 hours into the game and still feel I've barely touched half of it.This game is not for everyone! If you want your hand held and guided through your game, don't bother.If you’re looking for a in depth game that rewards those willing to put in effort and work at something, be it combat, crafting, exploring, dancing in a bar whatever floats your boat. This is it.While the game is Alpha at this stage with plenty of bugs and unfinished features it’s still more fun than any MMO I've played in years.  The Development team is the best I've seen in forever, the type I never thought I'd see again in this age of Early Access and Pay to Test.  Devs are on the forums actively responding to feedback, asking for information and actually listening to the community.  There are GMs online in shifts to trouble shoot issues and help gather documentation for the development team.  Really it’s something else.The game itself is complex. So complex one could get a panic attack just looking at the crafting of something as simple as a combat knife.  It takes some effort but all the tools are there and the community is excellent even for an Alpha group.  So it’s hard to go too in depth in a review about any feature without writing up a huge section so I’ll leave it with general statements.  There is ton of information on the site and forums if you’re interested in more details.Everything they advertise about the game is there and then some. It may not be fully fleshed out but the bare bones are there and one can get a clear idea of what the finished product will be.  It’s not like so many early access games, I’ve tried my fair share, that boost all these things they want then when you get in they have two or three things kinda working sorta and tons of features nowhere even on the horizon.   Repopulation at this stage has at least a skeleton of every major feature in place that I have looked into.  It needs a lot of fleshing out but it gives you a good idea of what they plan and that they are actually working to produce what they promise.Updates are common, It seems they have slowed down to about one a month.  Slowed down to what most people consider the “normal” rate and many times faster than what I have come to expect from Early Access games.  But don’t let that make you think it’s just some tiny little fix a few bugs patch.  The notes are huge. Tons of changes, bug fixes, balancing and fleshing out content in amounts that are staggering.  Again, this isn’t something we should be so shocked or awed about as it “should” be the norm.  But again we live in the early access era.  Final note on the patches, I don’t remember the last game I was as excited about patches as I am with this one.  They put up patch notes as soon as they release the current patch and add finished features ready for the next patch as it goes along.  Really nice to have a Dev team that isn’t “Vague” on what they are working on.If you do buy in know it’s not all peaches and cream.  There are bugs a plenty, crashes happen but the game is more stable than many “released” ones I’ve played recently.  It’s not optimized so at times it can be laggy, I have a pretty good rig so don’t notice it much.  Mostly when opening certain menus or entering a new zone.Combat is better than I thought but still needs tons of balancing and is fairly simple.  There is a system in place for stuff like this attack causes this debuff so you use this one to trigger this debuff ect that’s pretty decent but the fights are either really easy or really hard.  There are some open world “dungeons” in place to give you a feel for what they plan and it works rather well.  But it still has a long way to go.  It is kind of complex in the mixing of different armor’s and weapons combined with the flexibility of the fitting system to the point there is no “best” build as all will work well used right.Crafting is amazing. It’s why I first came here and I am not disappointed. It still needs some tweaks but it’s the first game in a long while where crafting wasn’t just important but the back bone of the game.If you’re like me you’ve been burned by the “Early Access” so many times you’d rather walk into traffic than try it again.This is the first one I’ve ever been truly happy with making my purchase and I wish I had started up sooner than later.The last thing I can say is out of all the games I’ve played on Steam over the years, this is the only one I was willing to take my precious game time to sit down and write a review for."
