76561198066258459,Recommended,322300,16541946,"Posted: 19 June, 2015",all,Pink,"6.19.15So far I've played the game for 12 hours, and so far it's everything I've been looking for from an MMO the last 5 years. YES the game is in alpha, but the content that is ALREADY in the game far surpases most mainstream MMO's on the market. Just looking through a list of the mechanics, it warms my gamer heart: for those searching for a 'hardcore' experience, this is where it's at.Each skill in the game is leveled through use, and as you use the skills and they increase, you open up the amount of skills you get on your action bar. Personally, this skill aquisition system is excellent. Not only are the skills not handed to you (you either have to purchase them with training points or receive as mission rewards) but the way you mold your character is completely up to you. This makes the combat highly customizable, allowing weapon swapping and combining skills and status affects.As far as the current state of the game, it is very much in alpha, and feels like it. The game is stable enough to play, but some of the features are not in the game (some skills, some missions, etc.) and there is a general clunkiness to everything. This game has me very excited for its future, the crafting is very in depth, the combat is fully customizable and can be switched between action and traditional rpg, and the overall feel of the game is unique and fresh but also nostalgic and genuine.3.25.17So the servers were shut down for a time (not going to go into details) but the game is back, and I am so excited. Everything is back to where it was before the servers went down so nothing new to report on, but you can tell this game is loved by how many people were yelling in general chat ""IT'S BACK"" more to come as the game hopefully progresses.Welcome back, repop!- I'll keep updating this as time progress."
