,Recommended,322300,13911742,"Posted: 9 January, 2015",all,-=Lonnisity=-,"Been waiting for this game ever since I heard it could potentially be a replacement for Star Wars Galaxies when it shut down. Seeing as how it's inspired by and borrows features from SWG, I would say that's true. The tutorial throws a ton of information at you at once, so if you think you can just fly through it your first time, you're going to be clueless once you're in the actual game world. I actually scraped my first character (which I completely rushed) and took my time with creation and the tutorial the second time around. The result was a much more stable and enjoyable experience, even though the game is in Early Access. I'm definitely going to be sticking around on this game.Gameplay: 8 ~ The Repopulation is an incredibly vast and detailed game, but with detail comes complexity. If you have enough self-control to take the time necessary to learn all of the game's mechanics in the tutorial, you'll have an enjoyable experience. It does feel a little stale in terms of combat, but that's an easy thing to overlook if you're having fun.Graphics: 8 ~ Lighting effects is where this game really shines (literally.) Though everything does have a sort of stylized-realism, (that is to say, mildly cartoony instead of Battlefield/CoD lifelike) it fits the overall feel of the game well, and I have no personal complaints.Sound: 8 ~ Continuing with my theme of ""It's quite good, but..."" Almost all of the sound effects in the game are incredibly well done. The only things that I have trouble with so far are player voice overs that spout cheesy one-liners whenever you increase your skill level, (Hint: You can disable voices) as well as the horrendously cheesy sound effect that's used for the starter pistol. It sounds like something straight out of an 80's sci-fi movie and I can't wait to get a better sounding pistol.Lasting Appeal: 10 ~ I remember reading in a feature on The Repop's website that basically offered a massive challenge. I'm paraphrasing, but it was something along the lines of, ""You could max out every single skill in the game, there's nothing restricting you to any set amount of skills. However, you never will."" If you spent your entire game experience on The Repopulation trying to max out all the skills, you would be set for a very very long time as far as content. There's so much to do, so many skills to try out, let alone progress to high levels. And with no class restrictions, you can do what you want, when you want, how you want, and as much as you want. That alone, to me, defines ""Lasting appeal.""Overall Rating: 9 ~ This game is in early access, meaning that polish is inevitable, which is coincidentally all that this game needs to be a top contender in the MMO market. I love it already, and can't wait to see where it goes from here."
