,Recommended,322300,16334467,"Posted: 12 June, 2015",all,obscurous,"Overall a great game. Remember that at the time of this review, it is still in alpha. They are starting to impliment the changes to the system designed for launch. Some of these changes are frustrating as the current population is not very high. You must look long term. Think about how the game will change when there are enough people to fill the auction house, place good solid work orders, and fight over resources. So before you slam a change made because it complicates things, think about how this will feel with 4-5X as many players per server.  Aslo keep in mind that a server whipe, merger, or refit could come without notice, so dont get attached to your toon.If you are thinking about playing this game at launch, you will want to jump in now and take a look around. The crafting system is super detailed and intense. The combat system is unique, and play style is completely different for each weapon and armor mix. Healers are still being give some polish, so if that is your thing come in now and help give some feedback."
,Recommended,322300,16631651,"Posted: 22 June, 2015",all,Skiptrace Starbound,"The Repopulation... Where to start?This game I heared about before it went into a playable Alpha state. And, it intrigued me. It's an MMOSBRPG, or Massively Multiplayer Online Sandbox Role Playing Game (Long Abbreviations FTW!). And, here's my review of this.Graphics: Current: 7.5/10 Future: ?/10: So, since this game is an alpha, I have to review what is given to me. And, it's pretty good, but I can't push the high quality, due to my machine not quite being able to play at max with a good framerate, though with the upgrades that I want to purchase, maybe then i'll be able to play at 144 FPS on Ultra for this game. The game looks nice, but the character animations are a bit lazy, but they will change with time. Oh, and Dual Wielding Pistols is really funky... You hold both pistols in the same physical location, leading to some funny clipping stuff.Overall Gameplay: 9/10Combat: 10/10: This game has such a unique combat system. It has one main governing system, the Openings System. If you shoot someone in the Leg, they are the suceptible to other things like maybe Bleeding, or if someone is Startled because of how close you got to them from a shot or slash, then maybe you can Dishearten them and make them deal less damage. Any way you slice it, this game does not have ""Basic"" attacks, each and every attack has some flavor of modifier. And that is really cool!Crafting: 7.5/10: Ok, this is the meat and potatoes of this game. I can't go over each aspect of crafting in this review, because it would be a 20 page college level paper... If you want the details, The Repopulation Forums are a great place to go to learn about crafting! Basically, you gather materieals, such as Contaminated Water, Hides, Wood, Berries, Metal Ores, etc. and process them into components to make other things, such as Fittings which will have their own spotlight in the next section. The main problem with the crafting is, there is soo much crafting that you will probably make your head explode trying to do it all, but fear not, you can still make money as a gatherer through the Work Orders system which will be talked about in it's own section.Gear System: 10/10: This game has a fantastic gear system that revolves around 100% Customization. Every Gear Item is a shell, you put Fittings into the shells to give them buffs such as Physical Resistance or Penetration, or Burning status effects, or more Health, or more Endurance, or more Momentum Retention, just about every stat in the game is given through Fittings you put in your Armor or Weapons.Auction House: 10/10: This is one of the best parts about the game, the ""Auction House"" It has several functionalities such as Work Orders and a plain auction house ripped straight from WoW. Work Orders allow gatherers and crafters to work together to get items in exchange for Credits (this game's currency) a Crafter can put out a Work Order from anywhere in the world (you can also buy and put things on the Auction House anywhere in the world) and a Gatherer or other Crafter can put in the items to fufill the Work Order and get a posted amount of Credits for their assistance.Final Verdict: 8.5/10: The game needs some polish definately, but this F2P MMOSBRPG I believe will become a titan in the industry that dominates over WoW and ESO, and SW:ToR. You can buy into the Alpha with the Silver and Gold Packages right here on Steam and get some extra benefits when the game goes live some time in Q4 of this year! But the game will be 100% Free To Play, with the cash shop being 100% Cosmetic Items Only."
