,Recommended,322300,17439722,"Posted: 8 August, 2015",all,ThatOneGuy,"I'll just say this before my review so that you have it in mind. My pc is well under-specced for this game and I have always given each patch a small bit of playtime before temporarily stopping. The lag is killing my brainwaves hahaPROS:1) The world is very open. This, itself, gives the player alot of freedom, though, I still dont see many people that leave the starting zones.2) This game is based mostly off of crafting. Actually this is a pro and a con, but for now, the pro part of it is that you can craft everything you would ever need if you have the patience and skill for it.3) Lots of skills, 87 different skills if I am correct. That means you can pretty much always have something to do and its solely up to you how you do it.4) Unlike most mmos where you have to grind for money, this game practically gives it away through quests, loot, and putting for crafted goods on the Auction House. For someone who plays a few hours a week, I can make about 15k in one sitting because of it.5) Player Housing. There are 3 forms of this but one of the ways to use this to your advantage is building a nation and a player built city for just your friends.CONS:1) Prepare to learn the command ""/unstick"". You will practically get stuck on every little crevice due to some bugs that haven't been resolved.2) Back to the crafting issue. This is very tedious and near quantum mechanics level of difficulty. Thankfully, the auction house can have pieces to help with this issue.3) There is still massive amounts of lag in towns and in some fields. It has been improving but its not quite at a level where its acceptable4) There is absolutely no direction after the tutorial. It plops you in the main game and basically makes you figure out what to do next.5) The tutorial is extremely long and rather boring. The first time I did it, I managed it with only minor loss to my patience. The second time, I passed out from exhaustion thanks to crafting haha.While there are many pros and cons left to this game, it does the game alot of injustice to point it all out. I would highly recommend this game, but would probably also recommend waiting for it to hit beta first. The game has a patch about once a month or every few months so small things are constantly being updated. Before you buy this game, check out some reviews on youtube to get a gist on what to expect."
