,Recommended,322300,17272652,"Posted: 28 July, 2015",all,Bizq,"Everyone talks about Star Wars Galaxies (SWG) and Ultima Online (UO). I have never heard of them so i don't know how good were they but as someone who has played tons of MMOs this is probably one of the best of them. But, is it for you?Things you should know before getting into early access:- As this is an early access, there will be a wipe before launch (which is pretty standard for any game with EA)- There are many bugs/glitches you may or may not encounter through this EA journey. (The support team is pretty active so make sure you report this bugs)- You are not paying to play the game (this will be a F2P game) but for an EA, which means you are here to help int he develovment of this game.Things you should consider before playing this game:- This is not your standard MMO. This means no forced questline, no grinding dungeons/instances for the best loot nor 'character level'.- This game focuses on crafting. Which means you are going to gather a lot, travel across many places and fight with NPCs to get the best gathering places.- You are probably going to grind a lot. Be prepared! At the time i'm writing this review it's been 30 hours of gameplay, and i still feel pretty new to the game. In any other game i would have already finished it or would be at least half way to end game."
