76561198041526233,Recommended,322300,14521884,"Posted: 17 February, 2015",all,MacDougal,"This game has a lot of potential. Many nice features including email mission system, and lots of skills to work on.The skill system makes a nice change from the level grind found in most mmo games, players are not limited to linear progression, providing they have the right skill and gear players can go anywhere to advance. The skill system also has the advantage of allowing players to tailor gameplay to their particular taste, no need to make alternate characters.However It's very unpolished at present and badly needs optimized to produce smoother movement and performance, opening the map makes the game lag like crazy, especially so in the already laggy city areas.The graphics are not the most pleasing to the eye, could do with more textures, art work and better lighting, and greater diversity of environment.The combat doesn't quite work, currently combat feels like you are fumbling around while trying to target mobs and activate abilities, even the fps mode combat feels stiff and awkward.While fighting mobs they get so close to your character that you are practicaly shooting at your feet while trying to keep them in target, some bad AI combined with the weird combat system makes for poor gameplay.Frankly they need to choose one combat mode or the other, trying to combine hotbar click combat and FPS combat through the same basic combat system is poor game design.Exploration of the game is made difficult because of the death respawn system, the zones are quite large, upon death you are forced to respawn from the nearest city spawn point, this means you have to travel a fair distance back to where you were exploring, an ability to bind in the world or a simple time out mechanism would significantly reduce the demoralizing effect that death currently has for players.Maps and waypoints ingame could use some refinement, making it clearer for players to find where their mission objectives are. Too much time is wasted trying to find mission objectives at present making some missions just not worth the trouble.The game features an elaborate crafting system which many crafters will love, however at the same time this is likely to put many others off, alternatives for gear and upgrades for the more casual player may be advisable."
