,Recommended,322300,16572854,"Posted: 20 June, 2015",all,King Aria,"Did you enjoy Star Wars Galaxies, Shadowbane, Anarchy Online, Everquest or Dark Age of Camelot back in the day? Did you enjoy the era where MMO's had more complexity to them? Well, chances are you will enjoy this title. It has everything that made old school MMO's great but with a modern touch.The problem with MMO's nowadays is that they all follow the same formula: quest, level up, get gear and loot. While this is an OK formula, I missed the more open-ended MMO's where you could go out and do what you wanted without having to follow a linear progressional path. The Repopulation does this right. Similar to SWG (Star Wars Galaxies), the developers made the game so that you could start off and get right into crafting without having to force yourself to do combat. You could do quests if you want, but you can also head right out and follow your destiny.Want to be a tradesman who earns an honest living building vehicles and houses? You can do that. Want to be one of hundreds of soldiers fighting a war on the battlefield? You can do that. Thing is with this game; there are so many features to it that it really feels like a living, breathing world. Although still in 'Early Access' it feels like a polished Alpha. Granted, there are still MANY bugs and quirks that need fixing. The game would not be acceptable to the average gamer. However, if you have that itch for an old-school MMO like I did, then pick this up. It'll scratch that itch.I can't speak for the future of this game, but there is a LOT of potential here. The world is quite large as-is and I have a feeling they're planning to expand it. What makes this game feel like an actual world is the complexity of it. It could well be a life simulator once it's released. Only time will tell.Based on what I've experienced so far and the promise this game shows, I have no choice but to rate it a solid 8/10. However, if they fix the bugs, clunky UI & map glitches and add a little more pizazz to the game, I'd give it a 10/10. This is THE MMO to play for any MMO gamer."
