76561198018306173,Recommended,322300,16981690,"Posted: 10 July, 2015",all,RockApe,"If you miss SWG, this is the game for you.  If you love open-world sandbox games, this is the game for you.Its Alpha.  Things are amiss.  Because its Alpha.  But there is still an incredibly rich experience to be had even at this early phase.  The Alpha community is generous, helpful and knowledgable.    Are there glitches, bugs, random CTDs and errors than require you to wait for a midnight server reset to unstick your character?  Yep.  It's Alpha.  These things happen.There isn't a lot of hand-holding.  In fact, a lot of critical documentation has yet to be implemented, but give the game a day or so to grow on you.  I'm a SWG day one vet and have quite a bit of exposure to sandbox games.  I was still mystified by many of the game's aspects.  Three days in, I had figured most of it out.Fair warning: the crafting system is incredibly deep and complex.  This isn't going to be like Galaxies where you can be self-sufficient after leveling a couple of Alts to Master.I have a couple of beginners 'tips:  There's an NPC doctor in the hospital who wants parasites that can be looted while mining or logging.  Grab the 10cr used logging saw and used mining drill and have at it.  Rise and repeat all the way to your fist vehicle.  Price are about 2K for a decent cycle.  Or buy a Light Assault Mech and get killed by a vulture.  I take that back, don't by the Light Mech.  Just buy a cycle.Anytime you get an Engagement Mission....head out and do it.  The rewards will be worthwhile.Don't start fights you can't finish....specifically with any NPC mob that has ""Medic"" in their name.  Serioulsy OP atm.8/10 currently.  I can't give it 10/10 because it's not quite finished and polished (because Alpha).  Entirely worth the 20 bucks for the basic level backer's pack and Alpha access.Do it."
