76561197983782857,Recommended,322300,13657084,"Posted: 27 December, 2014",all,Nvi'Wraith,"Edit: Game is much much better than when i made my first review (back on steam launch) optimization is much better, skills are better, mobs are better. everything i complained about in my first post has largely been improved.That said, the game still has it`s issues, but these huge updates keep coming which is good to see and i still have high hopes for the game if they can clean up a lot of the clunkyness. Still recommend.Bought the alpha, its great at it`s core, but needs A LOT and I mean A LOT of work to be done, it`s buggy as hell. Its crazily unoptimized. im using 970 gtx with i7 4770k haswell OCd to 4.2. and on bare minimum i get 120 fps (when standing still and not in town). It`s going to be atleast half a year until it goes to beta.Insane amount of bugs. ontop of the bad FPS/terrible optimization. pretty much everything you do has potential to bug out. the only thing that seems implemented and actually finished so far is the crafting (which is superbly done) Very confusing and time consuming. but really fun if you turn it into you own little quest/adventure to aquire materials.The combat is clunky at the moment, not the skills, but the monsters within the game, they have terrible pathing, they rubberband to all hell. Also regardless of what some videos look like, at this point in time the game looks like its from 1998. so dont expect amazing graphics.Tons of potential, F2P will also be the death of this game, it`s a botters heaven and will be exploited to all hell unless they figure something out.It is alpha, and for an alpha, i mean it`s really not that bad. but if any of you want to buy into and alpha and expect flawlessness. this is not the game to do so with.I personally like the game, and will recommend it, but for anyone looking for a polished early access game, this is not the one for you."
