76561198023416519,Recommended,322300,30759819,Posted: 26 March,all,Nitara,"** tl;dr: this game is in ALPHA but even in its present shape, it's an amazing game, and worth buying if you don't mind the bugs and crashes that come with an alpha game. **Repop is a sandbox MMO really only comparable to the heyday of Star Wars Galaxies, as others have said.  This is a good thing.  There is no deeper crafting system in an active MMO.  One can spend hours at a crafting station, putting together just the right components to get just the right item, piece by piece.  For example, my pharmacist breaks down all the tissue samples from her blasted/burnt/gassed victims into chemical compounds, and using specially enriched nanites, creates an infusion that fills an injector, which, when used, will have one of a vast array of effects depending on the compounds used in the infusion - from enhanced speed or better aim to becoming resistant to knockdown, or in the heat of battle, recovering health in a pinch, or restoring stamina, improving damage... multitudinous applications in just one delivery package.That's ONE school of crafting. A few final item recipes (comprised of a number of crafted components, reagents, etc).  To say there are many recipes in the many schools of crafting would fail to convey the scope of The Repopulation's crafting system in an absurdly laughable way.Here, let me help you :)http://aena.at/craftmap/craftmap.htmlI enjoy the combat as well, but it's a different flow from a vanilla stand-and-press-button-1-2-3 schtick.  It's fairly engaging, but to be honest, I'm still re-learning it."
,Recommended,322300,18622557,"Posted: 22 October, 2015",all,Twitch.tv/babydozier,"If you are a fan of older-school MMORPGs a la Star Wars Galaxs and Ultima Online, you will likely enjoy poking around in the Repopulation.Written during patch 15.10.1:This game is currently in alpha, so don't expect anything near completion in terms of most aspects of the game. Be that as it may, Repop offers an insanely deep and rewarding crafting system on which the entire economy of the server is built.Exploration, as of now, can get pretty boring. SWG had a HUGE lore advantage-- it made visiting random sites super rewarding because of their connection to the series. Repopulation doesn't have that. The world is super interesting, and there are plenty of mobs, but it could benefit from making exploration more rewarding.Regardless, it's still immensely fun.The combat is also great, and the skill system provides a HUGE variety of abilities.PvP is going to be amazing once things pick up. So buy this game and help pick it up!"
