76561198723844965,Not Recommended,322300,31388536,Posted: 26 April,all,Karrion NightStalker,"Time to update review.Graphics out of date, think 2003. Client in definite need of being cleaned up. Controls and targeting are temperamental at best. Barely survive a fight, need a second to recoup, your client and it's clunky controls have a surprise for you, you now have 3 more things that you've inadvertently attacked and are now headed to the cloning station. Driving along on your bike, randomly dismount for no apparent reason. Cross two zones, crash to desktop, in fact you'll spend more time logging into the game then actually playing it.Open Skill system pretty much means that eventually, no matter how long it takes everyone will have the exact same skills as everyone else. Which will have the end effect of no variation in combat, pve or pvp. It also means that everyone will eventually be able to craft everything in the game thus making participating in the economy pointless. It'll end up being like any other MMO out there that you seen where a handful of people will own the market doing the 1 credit undercut game.PVE in this game is pretty much go kill lair, for those that remember swg and the lairs there, you all know how boring this ends up being. Pretty much toss down 2 turrets stand back and watch the mobs get mowed down, then loot and harvest... Can we say YAWN.The open skill system also promotes solo play, being as you can do everything yourself why bother interacting with anyone else?Skill up on use system, yea that's right all you have to do is use an ability in any given skill set and it will raise the skill. Over all effect is, you can macro and afk any skill in the game to top level just takes a little time, but less time then actually playing the game. What's even more is you can raise several skills at once.. wanna raise crafting, entertainer, and various combat related skills at the same time while you sleep.. this skill up system allows it. What a novel idea for a game, no need to play it to advance, let your $30 controller play it for you while you sleep.What's even more is the crafting and gathering system is the same old type of system that you've experienced for the past 20 years, so don't get excited about any innovations here there are none.. In fact the community is so invested in 20 year old mechanics it's doubtful things will ever change. In fact the poor UI design will make you want to toss your computer out the window.All in all for a sandbox type game where they are supposed to promote interdependence and socialization they in fact do everything they possibly can to promote you to play solo and discourage interdependence and socialization.Open world PVP, to this day i cannot understand why game developers would limit themselves to a niche market, essentially cutting their customer base to a fraction of what it could otherwise achieve. Take any game that has multiple rule set servers you will see 20 servers, 5 of which will be forced/open pvp and the other 15 will be non-forced pvp relying on consensual pvp and then be split into 2 subgroups of normal and RP. What we learn from this is that only about 30% of the population really likes the forced pvp concept. So once again why would someone in the business of making games for profit limit their potential customer base? It's like cutting your own throat.Now this games does what you've seen in other games it splits the world up into Non-pvp and pvp areas and of course just like other games that have done this the best opportunity for resources for crafting are in the pvp only areas once again forcing someone that would otherwise not want to pvp to pvp. What's even more is this game has decided that if you want to build a player city or nation you once again are forced to pvp.. So essentially those that don't want to pvp end up cut off from a great deal of a game content that they are actually paying for, this is a bad concept that only allows the griefers and gankers to thrive, yet further destroying any chance of community.Overall with the open skill system removes individuality, the on use skill advancement promotes afk game play, the archaic graphics, and 20 year old approach to crafting, resource gathering along with the single point of sales and the forced pvp pretty much insures that you might as well go back to playing wow as you are not going to find anything interesting here.If this new development team were to have any chance at saving this game that should have been left to die they will need to completely gut it and rebuild it into a totally different game then when it started out.Save your $20, google tetris and you'll find more entertainment then you will with this game.As i sit here i have to wonder how many copyright infringements have been made in creation of this ""game""."
