,Not Recommended,322300,16278755,"Posted: 9 June, 2015",all,Feury,"This game has some serious potential.  It already has things I find as glaring deficits in most modern RPGs/MMORPGs: the basis for a robust economy,  a complex crafting system that requires specialization, cooperation, and market use (and abuse!). It has player housing, both instanced and open world. I thinik it will be interesting to see how these pan out in the long term.All this game needs now is a driver for demand:  A population that has a reason to need or want the large myriad of items that can be crafted.  How to draw a population? This is a no brainer.  Incorporate some features that other games have already done well: A good combat system, good end-game content, and good aesthetics options, both in character and the characters' possesions.  Character development is key in keeping players. The Repopulation still seems to be (understandably, given its developmental stage) lacking in these areas.  However, it is definitely one to keep an eye on in the coming months!For now, I don't recommend picking up this game.  While it is promising so far, it does have a long way to go in order to become viable.  If it ever gets to the point that I think it's worthwhile, I will update this review and change my recommendation!"
