76561197989270269,Not Recommended,322300,17442643,"Posted: 8 August, 2015",all,Combat Wombat,"Tried to love this game but it's clearly not ready at the moment and really should not be a paid early access. I may change my mind once it releases but currently, no, it's not a worthwhile purchase unless you specifically want to support the project. I wish Steam gave the option of a caveat and not just a yes/no choice in this matter as while i cannot recommend the game in it's current state, it is still something quite unique in the current mmo genre and is to be commended for trying to do something old school and not follow the usual mmo cookie-cutter path.The main problem is this game relies on an active community of players to drive the economy and the social aspects of the game, currently the population on EU is around 20-30 players at peak times which renders the ecnonomy sterile and the world more so.Their biggest problem and the main reason for this is there will be a server wipe pre-launch, so anyone who owns the game is staying away as there is no point in playing or progressing as it'll be wiped. This is cyclical as you can imagine. No players, no economy, no social aspects to a player economy driven social centric mmo.Additionally the likenesses made to SWG should be taken with a pinch of salt. SWG without the Star Wars aspect loses a massive amount of it's draw. The crafting in TR is touted as deep, but it's not really the case, it's just unnecessarily complicated.Players complain of lag and latency issues, which i also experienced although not as bad as some have claimed. My computer is high spec as well, It seems the issues are client side. Most likely poor optimisation but this is to be expected from an alpha really.The combat is one of it's biggest flaws, i have hopes they will improve it pre-launch but right now it's pretty basic, glitchy and feels extremely dated and clunky. For a game that claims to emulate SWG it's mildly annoying that it's combat is inferior to a game that predates it by about 12 years.With beta approaching i still have hopes the devs will step-up and fix the multitude of problems, but the real issue for me is its impossible to know how this game will be come release. If nothing changes, it might be a serious flop and thats a concern for anyone invested in games of this type."
