76561198075785660,Not Recommended,322300,13669827,"Posted: 28 December, 2014",all,Kailash,"I really wanted to like this game, I have been following its progress for a few years, I like Sci-Fi, MMO's and sandbox games so this really should be a hit with me.Game: The graphics, animations and game play are bad. I understand this is early access and the final Alpha testing phase but that does not account for how bad the core game looks and feels. There are bugs, which is understandable, these can be ironed out and fixed through the Alpha and beta. The mob AI and pathing is very weak but I believe I did see a post from the dev's saying this is one thing to be updated later. The graphics and game play however, I think the game needs to go back to square one with a new engine and artists (Trying not to be rude to the artists, but they really should look into something called colour! Large portions of  grass, mountains, buildings are black, which is also the primary colour for players and most mobs. Seriously it hurts my eyes at times.) The performance seems rather poor, given there are very few NPC's and players. I expect spikes, crashes and disconnects but being stood still with players/mobs jerking past in the open is not what I would expect, nothing seems to flow smoothly.Crafting: Very complicated, too complicated for an average gamer I imagine. Personally I don't mind this, I think it can help the community stronger, force players and nations to work more closely.  It is very confusing and I would hope to see more detailed tutorials played out in the beta's. Where crafting falls down is that you obviously need to gather materials before you can craft; Gathering is boring, looting the same flower three or four times, killing mobs in mind numbing combat, running around an ugly world. I struggle to find a reason to explore when everything looks so bad right now.Sandbox: My “sandbox” experience was rather disappointing. The first training zone seemed a small instanced area and then loaded into a new city area. A quest in this city sends you to visit an apartment/tower block, which was also instanced! A building in the main city is instanced, even though it seemed to lead to one room with one NPC? Then there were quests to go to another zone and housing area which are also seemed to be separate instances/areas.Conclusion:For modern day gamers and MMO fans, I would advise avoid this game, certainly for this phase. I think the game requires a large investment of resources to make the graphics and game play enjoyable.  I believe The Re-population, as things stand, will have a small niche market of retro ex Star Wars galaxies fans who really don't mind playing something without the graphics and game play we have come to expect from games in the last 10 to 15 years.Personally I will check back in a few months to see how the artists have changed the textures, colours, animations and how smooth the game runs; hopefully I will come back and find the game has ported over to the CryEngine – then I’m sure I will be happy."
