,Not Recommended,322300,13618047,"Posted: 26 December, 2014",all,Pinkeh,"Revised my review with a bit more detail.Purchased after reading the description, seeing a few videos and thought i might give it a go. It is too early to tell given the state of the current game. Keeping in mind that Steam doesn't offer refunds, the price of entry into the Early Access build and the general state of the game right now, my recommendation is NO.After 10 hours of playing this game i can not recommend this game in its current state. Knowing that it is in alpha you expect problems, bugs or things that just dont work. Well a lot of things don't work and it makes it very difficult to enjoy the alpha build.The main draw of this game is going to be the extensive crafting system which will requires lots of time and resources to get to. Not going in to that in 10 hours of exploration/experimentation.GAMEPLAY ISSUES- Graphics: It's like we went back in time to 2004. The graphics are dated, the textures are muddy, it looks quite horrible. I don't think I can stand much more than 1-2 hour sessions at a time. Frame rates dip drastically between zones when i assume loads new assets into the game, but then the client stutters and freezes and continues to do so until you quit the application and restart.- Crafting requires lots of experimentation, which also means that you have to spend hours gathering material or killing things. Not seeing much fun in either ventures in the current build. Some people love this sort of thing but I don't see the point in spending so much time to build a basic weapon early on. Sucks all the fun out of the game for casual crafters.- Background Music: I turned it off. It was quite annoying.- Controls / UI: Clunky. Half of the time all the buttons stop animating so you have to reset the game to resolve UI glitches. WASD makes the character move, but the camera leaves little to be desired. When walking into rooms with low ceilings i tend to clip the floors or have to zoom into first person to see anything. I play the game at isometric aerial view because it gives me better spatial awareness. Playing over the shoulder or in first person gives me headaches.- Poor navigation / pathfinding: The game needs better cartographic elements. Symbology is also rubbish. The mini map also do not reflect the landmarks on the ground so it's a constant struggle to find important NPCs and places of interest. Developer needs to take cartographic lessons and map making classes. You're expected to use your tracking skill to locate certain NPCs, man i could not be bothered after an hour or so running around the city spamming that tracking button.- Frustrating learning curve because of cryptic tutorials / quest information. Job offered to player: Go to A and pick up package to delivery to B. No information as to where A or B is. Up to you to track down A and figure out where B is. Reward is not worth the effort.- No audio feedback: Fire a weapon, no audio. Monster attacks you, no audio.- Questing system is a chore, and you struggle to do basic fetch, delivery and kill quests because of insufficient information. These are staple game mechanics in sandbox MMOGs and it struggles to even deliver basic missions.- Looting needs to be quicker. Right now it takes up to 5 seconds to begin the looting process, then a window takes over the screen. If you cross into the path of another beast, you begin your attack rotation but then the loot screen from your previous action blocks your view. You die.- Extracting process needs to be quicker/efficient. Took me a long time to figure out what ""enhance corpse"" and ""enrich nodes"" meant. It is more of a hassle in hostile zones too because you're taking around 30 seconds between corpses trying to improve the grade of the corpse, and then you cross the path of a hostile  roaming player / monster, and you die.- On the advice of many people playing the alpha, I skipped the crafting and focused only on combat jobs and killing things. There are other job offers that are sent to your mailbox but I lost all motivation to do them because of the struggles with finding NPCs and places of interest.COMBAT- Roleplayed a sniper. Take a rifle out in to the woods. Interesting that the damage varies depending on distance between you and the target. Problem arise when monster agro circle is larger than the optimal range of my weapon. So you run into the monster's range, it starts attacking you before you can pull off your first shot. The monster is in your face and you're doing minimal damage. You die.- Automatic weapons is ok, but the optimal range is basically in your face. If you're not heavily armored, you die.- Didn't try other weapons.- Found a level 26 goat in a level 10 zone. Didn't realise it was that much more difficult until I agro'd it. What's up with that? I don't mind that a higher level monster is in the zone, but nothing indicates that it was more difficult until I started attacking it (the ""level"" of the monster didn't show till it was attacking me) and obviously i died.RECOMMENDATIONAt this stage i do not recommend it. The alpha build is not fun and there are many gameplay elements that do not do the current build any favours.It is currently not worth my time to continue testing as it was quite disappointing.Picked up the game during Steam 2014 Christmas sales at $33. I regret this purchase when there are alternative sandbox MMOGs available."
