76561198003862678,Not Recommended,322300,14677787,"Posted: 27 February, 2015",all,EMax,"BUYERS REMORSE:As a long time hardcore player of SWG I was excited by the hype and anticipation for this game and have followed its development since 2012.  When I saw early access on steam I opened my wallet and decided to give it a go... it took me a single session of frustration to realize what a mistake I had made and what a lie the advertising has been.Where to start... well first thing you will notice is character creation.  Simply put, it is awful.  It is one of those systems that is intended to make the player feel like you have unlimited customization but in the end still cannot produce the result you want.  The player is given lots of meaningless options but even then it is frustrating to control (more on this later) as it is one of ""those"" character creators where adjusting one slider pushes three others.  Character design is ultimately unappealing so you better like wearing your helmet.  The entire character creator (and the character models for that matter) needs to be rebuilt from the ground up IMO.My next and probably largest complaint is with the controls and interface.  Much like character creation, we are given the illusion of lots of choice, but none of the choices we want or need.  I found myself wrestling with the controls constantly... not a good sign and it really takes away from getting into the game.  Remember the smooth, user friendly controls and interface from SWG that felt good to the touch and allowed you to become easily immersed in the world?  Apparently this design team does not.  Being able to ALT between mouse mode and third person would be a huge step in the right direction, but merely scratching the surface of what requires a complete overhaul.Graphics:  Well, in fairness one should not expect too sophisticated of graphics from any MMORPG if you want complexity in the world while maintaining playability.  But some of the design choices here are just.... baffling.  The aspect ratios and fonts are such that I was suffering eyestrain and a headache after a mere 2 hours of play.  On top of that, the world is drab and lifeless aesthetically.  All browns and greys.  Lots of darkness.  It simply does not LOOK interesting.  Already mentioned that the characters look like garbage.  I do not kid that in addition to the physical discomfort I felt a bit depressed after playing for a couple hours from looking at such an uninspired landscape and world.The game world is horribly scaled, a trend I see shared with more and more MMOs of recent times.  By this I mean, every structure you enter is enormous and out of proportion... large vacant spaces with colossal head space and lots of meaningless filler.  Remember in SWG, you would enter a structure and the proportions made sense?  The rooms were filled with items in what appeared a logical and meaningful way?  When you walked the streets of say, Coronet, nearly all of the buildings had some function and the scale of it all made sense?  This new style of MMO world gives us big, vacuous structures meant to provide the illusion of vastness.  It asks you to walk 3 minutes from one drab structure which is identical to the next in order, save for some stupid billboard outside.To further compound the frustration of the experience, I could still feel the ""rails"" beneath it all.  This game is by no means a true sandbox in any sense.  It may have some sandbox-like qualities, but to compare it to SWG is an insult.  I was getting more of a ""Star Trek Online"" and ""Old Republic Online"" vibe from this game.  If you are a fan of those games but prefer a drab, lifeless, brandless sci-fi setting, then this may be the game for you.If you came looking for the next SWG...... ""move along""."
