76561198094812371,Not Recommended,322300,14082446,"Posted: 20 January, 2015",all,Volkoth,"I know this game is in Alpha, and they have many disclaimers posted all over the game and on Steam stating the game is in Alpha. We are told to expect bugs and an overall unfinished product. This game will be a free to play business model whenever it finally 'releases'. As such, I don't know what possessed me to plop $40 of my hard earned money on this game, and I sincerely wish I could get a refund.First, before the Fanboys start the flaming, let me say I am a hardcore SWG fan and played the game from initial release until the end, and let me say this game does a good job at recreating the general feel of SWG right down to the UI. But something is lacking.I find it ireprehensible that this game is in such a horrid state of development after the amount of money people have pourd into it and the amount of time the game has been in development. The development of this game began in 2008...yes, almost seven years ago. It's 2015 now and we are no closer to release then we were in 2010 when they switched engines for this game.The problems of this game start in character creation. with the general premise of the game, I understand there is only one race, humans. Thats fine. The issue is in the general lack of options. The control scheme in creation isnt very intuitive, and your face always looks the same. The only real way to change the general look is to make your character fat or skinny and slap facial hair on them. Even after that they still look like shiny claymation characters.Then you get in the gameworld and get to stumble through the shoddy tutorial. SWG honestly had better graphics and ran jus as choppy. and how old is SWG. Also, when you get in game you realize the terrain is horrendous, the rocks and stones look like cardboard and the grass looks like pipecleaners. The town's feel vacant. Most NPC's don't serve a purpose or show any signs of AI. When you get into combat, the laser effects are downright cheap and goofy.The premise for this game is great, the vision is epic and the spirit of SWG is there, but after close to seven years of development and a lot of consumer investment, I expect better than this rough shod heap. If you are thinking about paying $40 for an Alpha, remember it's an alpha...seriously. And there are no signs after playing it there will be a release any time soon."
76561198018453980,Not Recommended,322300,14927272,"Posted: 16 March, 2015",all,Osiris,"Going to have to give this a thumbs down in it's current state.I will revisit the game in several months and see if it merits a change to this review.The game has overly complex, poorly implemented, and poorly defined game mechanics.Entry barriers, to do anything other than shoot stuff, are very high.The crafting system is very complex, overly so, and relies on an in game database that is hard to navigate and only vaguely describes the processes required.Combat is very weak, especially melee, and the mob ranking system is convoluted.(sometimes a mob is easy to kill and sometimes the same mob will kill you in one hit because you forgot to take time to mouse over every mob and decipher the bizarro rank system)2/3rds of the maps are PvP, only 1/3rd of the game maps are available to players that do notwish to PvP.The mapping system is both weird and broken, needless arrows constantly popping up, can't find mission goals some of the time. The minimap is completely useless and I covered it with the shift-m map (because the regular M map is totally trash no one uses it).The housing system is not easy to use and provides nothing in the way of storage, it has no benefit except to set up a player store and that store can only be used if players stumble across it or you have sent them a waypoint to find it.Progression is based on repeatedly using a skill and will require many, many, hours to gain ground. (casuals will not progress much)Every activity is super grindy, you will have to spend dozens of hours searching and gathering before you can make even simple items.The mission system is the same, repeat, repeat, repeat, with most missions just running back and forth for very little reward.The game will cater only to the hardcore that can spend many, many, hours in game.If you have no life, no job, no family, this game will help to fill that emptiness.The UI is poorly implemented, windows are not locked to screen edges, text overlaps and overruns windws and text on the mission review is so small it is nearly impossible to read.It's graphically at least a half dozen years out of date, characters are truly ugly and the maps are quite dull and colorless (with the exception of dull green/brown.)Character animations are absolutely awful, very amateur.Zone lines are the worst I have ever seen in an MMO, textures do not match and it is a horrific stutterfest of 2 FPS crossing them.(oh what fun to stutter across a zone line only to be insta killed by a plant...)Runs on the Hero engine...I understand this is an ""alpha"" but as it sits this game has too many weaknesses and a super grind style gameplay that will only appeal to a small number of people.Do I regret spending $15 on this game ?No.Would I buy it given what I know now ?No."
