76561197965028239,Not Recommended,322300,14393332,"Posted: 8 February, 2015",all,Mac68,"If you don't like crafting constantly don't play it. If you don't like unnecessarily complicated crafting, don't play it. If you don't like spending the majority of your in-game time harvesting resources of unnecessarily largley varying ""quality"", don't play it.Let's also dispel the myth that this is SWG reborn. Nonsense. I played SWG for years and this game does not even come close. In some ways it is similar, but so are other games. Yet still it seems that nobody has learned the positive lessons SWG put out there about sandbox games.Crafting is an absolute joke. To make one simple T1 component (one of several needed to make a basic item) is a real exercise in patience and/or frustration. The game relies on you being able to by certain parts or resources from other players, and you can't. Not with the current player base at least. All crafting is also carried out at a generic crafting station that seems capable of such diverse tasks from bio engineering to simple woodwork. Ridiculous.Combat is dull and uninteresting. It has 2 modes, classic rpg and ""action"" (direct aim etc). Neither of them work particularly well. And watching the trajectory of your high powered sniper rifle bullet as it bends and twists it's flight path (slow one at that) to follow your target like some sort of mini homing missile, gets rather annoying after a while.Lots of missions to do, all the same thing though. They repeat over and over and over.The world is large, looks ok, and is well populated by some imaginative denizens. Most of which will tear you to pieces early on when you get sick and tired of running around the same city for ages and attempt to go somewhere else.The stats system? Stupid. Its all down to whatever ""fittings"" you slot in your armor and weapons. I think this is a pre-cursor to a free2play model in the future where fittings will be available in some kind of ingame store etc. I don't know.All in all, a bad game with great potential. It is boring and repetitive when starting out, you cant craft anything worth while and will spend most of your time chopping logs just to make some money to repair gear or buy fittings. It will not hold the interest of anyone of average intelligence for long. Watch this space though, it could get better. For now though, save your money. This game is not worth anywhere near the asking price. Its still in early access of course, but nevertheless, not worth the same cost as a full release game"
