,Not Recommended,322300,15526855,"Posted: 24 April, 2015",all,Plaguewielder,"So after being a leader of two of the largest and greatest nations in the game (first Raiders of Muspelheim and secondly Tanstaafl Alliance) I really do have to give it a thumbs down.  I understand there were a lot of issues with Hero Engine but, really no one should have been left in the dark for so long.  I poured my heart and soul into this game and sometimes put up with more than I should have just because of blind faith.  There were nights where it took me 5 or 6 attempts to log in without crashing, then to travel and crash and restart that cycle of log in, crash, log in, crash, log in, crash, log in, load world, crash. Disapearing items, broken combat, broken crafting, and tormentingly complex systems for crafting all kinda wore me out and made me quit.  I only stayed around for my nation.After a while though as population on the servers died and became barren there was no more reason to stay around.  Everyone left due to engine issues, again I don't blame Repop for this.Now with the game practically dead they have announced that they're releasing a new game on the unreal engine... which seems pretty sweet!  It seems like it may actually be a winner... but, will it be free to those who bought Repopulation?  Or are we getting more hands in our wallets?  I feel bad for the people who put money into buying the higher level packages... I only bought three copies of this game.Only time will tell but, currently Repop is dead to me."
,Not Recommended,322300,13883846,"Posted: 7 January, 2015",all,Cap'N Squirrel,"07/21/15 - (Edited) Review 35 Hour review (15 with new patch)I want to start out by saying that I REALLY REALLY wanted to like this game (for many years), but at last I can't have any more faith in it. The bugs that persist are trivial to fix yet remain for years on end. The combat balance is... horrible at best. Finally, at the 35th hour, I can't be bothered to follow this developer or this title any longer.This game still needs a LOT of work, but has come a LONG WAY (although some of it is backwards)!!It has a lot of promise if the developer could only get a real team together but it is very much in it's pre-alpha stages (after many years in development). To be fair it has made some improvements in the last six months, but it has yet to address some very basic design flaws (which leads me to believe the developer desires it in this state. ""Working as intended"").I would highly suggest following its progress if you are still uncertain, but dont expect much. There are a lot of balance issues still, loads graphic glitches, but the character models/animations are better, but they can still use some final polish.Final Verdict: PUT YOUR CASH ELSWHERE.It's good if you want to help with the development. This title has been ""in the works"" for years and as such it is an old engine. This poses a lot of problems for the devs and they do tackle the issues, but there is only so much they can do. They are not there yet however (after YEARS), and the game is still clunky and glitchy as hell.Because of how long this title has been in ""Alpha"" and how old the engine is, I cannot in good conscious recommend paying the price they are asking. Wait for a sale, test it out, and return it if you can’t run it.I honestly hope the devs step up the progress on this title, but I’m not sure that will happen.THE PLUSES:-  More depth on systems that was already deep.-  Added Mini-games for Non-combat professions which show great promise.-  Added a better flowing ""Newbie Stage"" making an introduction to the game systems better explained (and fun).-  They improved the character models/animations (still needs some more choices and work).The old Pluses-  The Newbie Area is much better, but still has a lot of problems.-  There is quite a bit of depth to the game and how you as the player would want to play it.-  The world is vast.-  The Crafting is vast (VERY VAST)-  The questing is pretty fresh and has a lot of promise, (but still needs al lot more work)-  TONS of skill trees to explore (best part of the game!)-  Lots of room for growth as a game stillTHE CONS:-  BUGS - BUGS - BUGS! Lots of them. More than before.-  WAY over designed!-  Graphic Issues, Lock-ups, Video Lag, and random crashes (worse than before).-  Environment and level Design is better, but not perfect (loads of stuck player areas)-  The engine connection still lags quite a bit.-  HORRIABLE video lag (and logic lag if you can believe that).-  Targeting is still difficult in combat leading to frustration.-  NPC AIs need a tremendous amount of work (Epically where LOS is concerned).-  Town and Cityscapes need a graphical overhaul.-  Horrible combat balance-  Old Engine-  Masses of mobs causing the player to get swarmed or leave them with nothing to hunt.-  UI is garbage and full of bugs.-  Art is subpar (comparing it to gamed from 2005)."
