,Recommended,322300,16749043,"Posted: 27 June, 2015",all,Antagonist,"This is one of those rare instances where an early access game gets abandoned, and then the developers come back to it. In fact, if I'm not mistaken, this is the only such instance. So I am changing my ""Do not Recommend"" to ""Recommended"".What makes this game any different than any others? Depth. There is so much depth to this game, that it would be impossible to learn it all in even a month. There are thousands of recipes, billions of combinations of what you can do. A deep crafting system and a cool sci-fi world to play in.The game still needs some work, but after being gone for almost a year or more, I suspect not much was done during that time. They always promised it would come back, but if you've played early access before, you've heard that line before. I am impressed with these developers that they actually made good on their promise.I've heard this compared to Star Wars Galaxies, and I think that is a fair comparison. I would maybe throw Ultima Online in there as well. There is so much to do that it would be impossible for you to do it all yourself, which forces you to actually be social and play with other people.I was very disappointed when the game went down, and when I was told today it was back I was very excited to play. Unfortunately, as of right now, the game is EXTREMELY laggy. I have faith they will fix this issue. Their initial reason for shutting down was because of some kind of legal rights with the engine, again, I thought it was a lie. But seeing them coming back, even though they had already made a ton of money, shows integrity. The developers are very helpful and friendly as well when you contact them in game.So if you're looking for a highly complex sci-fi MMORPG, this is what you've been looking for.Just be warned, this game has a STEEP learning curve. Perhaps the steepest learning curve of any game I've played besides EVE. I think Repop is better, but that's opinion.Ultimately, it's up to you if you decide to get it, but this is not the game you just hop in and play casually. You can play casually, but you're going to forget stuff because there is so much to do.If you get it, I think you will enjoy it. And you always have 2 hours (or 2 weeks, whichever comes first) to get a refund, so you literally have nothing to lose by trying it."
